5:
...Are you sure there are lingering
emotions in this place? I can't sense
anything, but...
8:
You kidding? There's so much hate
and pain here, I don't think there's a
single spot without some kind of
nasty emotion!
11:
I can't believe I never noticed this
treasure trove until now! This is the
mother lode of juicy info!
16:
...Aren't you worried that someone
who hated you might have left
something behind too?
19:
Oh, please! I never leave a trace, so
how would they know it was me to
blame—
22:
That voice sounded familiar. I guess
it was a nonzero chance that I'd
eventually run into someone I know,
huh?
29: Who do you think it is?
31:
An old boss of mine? My old man?
Or maybe an old childhood friend?
34: ...Do you actually have any of those?
37:
Well, my old boss is still alive,
working on a fishing boat in Tiatha,
so can't be them!
42:
...Are you really going to leave it
alone? What if you get cursed by
something even worse?
46:
Haha, worried for little ol' me? You're
too kind for your own good—
50:
So, nobody came to your rescue
when you lost your place in society.
52:
You clung onto the organization you
joined, only to be used and abused.
You died completely miserable.
55:
Now you're afraid of me, because I
just learned all that about you.
58:
That's fine. We can put an end to
this. No need for embarrassment
then.
60: So go on. Get out of here.
69:
Hahaha! Who knew I had it in me?
Looks like even the dead can be
tricked with words!
76:
Ohhh, now that's interesting! Thanks!
Wonder how I can put that info to
use...
80:
Is this really the best use of your
time? I thought you were trying to
be the number one informant in the
world.
84:
What do you mean? There's nothing
more powerful than getting
information that no one else has
knowledge of!
86:
I get to toe the line and have
everyone else dance to my tune! It's
just the best!
94:
What's there not to get? If you ask
me, you're the one that's hard to
understand.
98:
What's the point of picking a fight
with those Overlords or whatever?
100:
You've got plenty of connections.
You could just shore up your
defenses and keep safe.
104:
...You still won't get it, even if I give
you my answer. But I'll try anyway.
106:
There's plenty of reasons for me to
choose this path, but if I had to pick
one...
108:
It's because I can't stand sitting
around when I can be doing
something instead.
111: Is that the sort of info you wanted?
114:
Info's info, especially since anything
about you sells for a lot.
121:
There's such a thing as being too
modest, Alk.
123:
You're more valuable than you give
yourself credit for. Consider that
both a word of warning and advice.
127:
Hmm... Alk, can you take a look at
this?
130:
The lingering emotions of the dead
are drawn to this knife.
134:
...This has to be a cryptic artifact. It
kind of reminds me of yours,
actually.
138:
Hey, want to know something fun? I
bet you do, right? You know you do.
141:
...When have I ever said yes to
wanting information from you?
145:
You know the Star Augurs, yeah? The
organization you occasionally run
into.
148:
They're responsible for the
distribution of most of these
artifacts, at least at the top. They've
got quite the reach.
150:
I've definitely poked my nose into
their business without meaning to
before.
158: Anyhoo, I'll be taking this knife.
161:
Gotta use everything I can,
otherwise it'd be a waste, right?
167:
...Just the other day, I heard that a
merchant illegally selling cryptic
artifacts got arrested.
170:
Apparently, someone tipped the
Guild Knights off and gave them
plenty of evidence.
182:
Now why would you think that? An
upright citizen like me wouldn't know
shady people like that.
186:
Says the guy who just warned me
about the Star Augurs. Why'd you
give me that info anyway?
188:
Isn't it obvious? Times like these, you
need some safety nets.
192:
Even I need an ally or two
sometimes.
196:
And allies get special deals from
me! If you ever need any info, I
might be able to help!
203:
The thought of being in debt to you
terrifies me to no end.
208:
Now that's a top tier compliment for
an informant! I can't wait to do more
business with you, pal!
